        {
            "id": "7312898e7f7741e5bd9a0",
            "questionText": "A delivery drone takes off from a warehouse. It ascends vertically for $!$10\\,s$!$ at a constant acceleration of $!$2\\,m/s^2$!$, then flies horizontally at a constant velocity for $!$30\\,s$!$ to deliver a package. After dropping the package, it decelerates horizontally at a rate of $!$1\\,m/s^2$!$ for $!$15\\,s$!$ before landing. Calculate the total distance traveled by the drone during its flight.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "d64e3a8c4f7f45f6914d7",
                    "stepText": "Let's begin by selecting the correct formula to calculate the vertical distance traveled during the drone's ascent (starting from rest with constant acceleration). Identify the proper expression that relates displacement, acceleration, and time.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "976c240a-1fbe-4cc3-bec4-a1cd6c0c9f6a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = ut + \\frac{1}{2}at^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = u + at$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = \\frac{v^2 - u^2}{2a}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "d18e08ec26d44754b2c5d",
                    "stepText": "Now, consider the deceleration phase. Since the drone comes to rest in $!$15\\,s$!$ due to a deceleration of $!$1\\,m/s^2$!$, use the relation between acceleration and time to compute the constant horizontal cruise speed.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "15"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "976c240a-1fbe-4cc3-bec4-a1cd6c0c9f6a"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "fa2428c194e34ddc86226",
                    "stepText": "Next, calculate the horizontal distance covered during the cruise phase. Use the constant cruise speed and the cruise time of $!$30\\,s$!$ to determine this distance.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "450"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "4e975fd0-c8b9-4ea7-a7f2-e68f006ffbfb"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "d78d567cfa8f46bea2091",
                    "stepText": "Now, select the correct formula for determining the horizontal distance traveled during the deceleration phase when the drone slows down from the cruise speed to rest. Identify the proper expression that includes the initial speed, time, and deceleration.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "976c240a-1fbe-4cc3-bec4-a1cd6c0c9f6a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = v_i t - \\frac{1}{2}at^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = v_i t + \\frac{1}{2}at^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = \\frac{v_i^2}{at}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
